result.name: Tai Chi Lo

reviews.text: Down to earth Shanghai cuisine. Inexpensive yet delicious food.  With many windows and very spacious
food quality is average, cleanliness should improve.  However to compare to its  low price which is understandable.

A rare restaurant for Shanghai cuisine in Chai Wan.  Set lunches in particular are of good value. The tea they served are of the same taste regardless of  kind of tea you ordered. The place is decidedly under staff during lunch hour. It was a different story in the evening. Food is good, generous portion,  enough staff to give you speedy service. I must add that the ceiling is about 2 stories high,  coupled with floor length windows, give the place a very roomy feeling.

result.name: Youth Square

reviews.text: Beautiful place for concerts and movie. A bit far from town but it’s only 3mins walk of MTR exit E, and bus station behind got all major routes to Kowloon side and Airport too.
A Modern multi-storied building near Chai Wan MTR station
With the proximity to Chai Wan MTR Station, The Youth Square has an exhibition located on the 5th floor showcasing a collection of printing arts and old machineries.

I discovered this place by accident and was so glad I did. Apart from the free WiFi, it has clean public washrooms. The best part is the cultural events, I got to watch some performances by local artists and visited a great exhibition on letter-press printing.
Many books
